# JPA Domain Entities

## Core JPA Rules
- Table prefix: `pp_`
- Use database sequence for primary keys (`@GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.SEQUENCE)`) with `@SequenceGenerator(allocationSize = 25)` — enables Hibernate batch inserts
- Use `ZonedDateTime` (UTC) for system timestamps, `LocalDate` for calendar dates
- Do NOT define indexes via `@Index` — indexes are managed by Flyway
- Do NOT use `@Column(length = ...)` — Flyway migrations define column sizes
- `@Column` should carry: `name` (always), `nullable` (when needed), `columnDefinition` (for TEXT) — nothing else
- Avoid bidirectional relationships unless necessary
- No business logic inside entities

## Lombok — Standard Domain Entity Stack

**Never use `@Data` on JPA entities** — it generates wrong `equals()`/`hashCode()`/`toString()` for lazy-loaded proxies.

```java
@Entity
@Table(name = "pp_table_slots")
@Getter
@Setter
@NoArgsConstructor
@EqualsAndHashCode(onlyExplicitlyIncluded = true, callSuper = false)
public class TableSlot extends BaseEntity {
    @Id
    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.SEQUENCE, generator = "table_slot_seq")
    @SequenceGenerator(name = "table_slot_seq", sequenceName = "pp_table_slot_seq", allocationSize = 25)
    @Column(name = "pk_table_slot")
    @EqualsAndHashCode.Include
    private Long id;
}
```

**Required:** `@Getter`, `@Setter`, `@NoArgsConstructor`, `@EqualsAndHashCode(onlyExplicitlyIncluded = true, callSuper = false)`, `@EqualsAndHashCode.Include` on `@Id`

**Forbidden:** `@Data`, `@AllArgsConstructor` (unless concrete need), `@ToString` without `@ToString.Exclude` on lazy associations

**Why `callSuper = false`:** `BaseEntity` has `createdAt`/`updatedAt` — timestamps should NOT affect equality.

## BaseEntity Auditing

All domain entities **must** extend `BaseEntity` — do NOT manually add `createdAt`/`updatedAt` fields.

- `@CreationTimestamp` / `@UpdateTimestamp` handle timestamps automatically
- UTC configured globally via `spring.jpa.properties.hibernate.jdbc.time_zone=UTC`
- Do NOT write `@PrePersist` / `@PreUpdate` callbacks
- Do NOT use `ZoneOffset.UTC` or `ZonedDateTime.now(ZoneOffset.UTC)` in entities
- Lookup entities (`entities/lookups/`) do NOT extend `BaseEntity`

## Enum Handling (Dual-Layer Pattern)

**Internal enums** (statuses, types owned by this service):
- DB lookup table entity (`pp_<enum>s`) with `id`, `name`, `description`
- Java enum with `getEnum(String)` method
- Reference via FK (`@ManyToOne`) — do NOT use `@Enumerated(EnumType.STRING)`

**External enums** (from other services like `ShiftCode`):
- Use `@Enumerated(EnumType.STRING)` — no lookup table needed

### Enum Design — Avoid Redundant `value` Fields
Use `name()` when the string representation == constant name. Only add a `value` field when the string differs (spaces, special chars).

```java
// ✅ No value field needed
public enum Gender {
    MALE, FEMALE, MIXED;
    public static Optional<Gender> getEnum(String value) {
        for (Gender g : Gender.values()) {
            if (g.name().equalsIgnoreCase(value)) return Optional.of(g);
        }
        return Optional.empty();
    }
}

// ✅ Value field needed — string differs from name
@Getter
public enum ApplicationRole {
    WFM_TEAM_LEVEL_1("WFM TEAM LEVEL 1"), GP("GP");
    private final String value;
    ApplicationRole(String value) { this.value = value; }
}
```

## Transaction Boundaries
Transaction rules are defined in the **Service Layer Guidelines** (`services.mdc`) — transactions are a service concern, not an entity concern.
